subSubSection.paragraph:
Prosternum (
Fig. 1B
):

prepisternum
with a few long, sparse setae on outer face; 
prepimerum
with a few sparse bristled punctures; 
prosternelum
rhomboidal, with acute base.

Elytra (
Figs. 1A, C
):

approximately 2.5× longer and 1.1× wider than pronotum; 
striae
narrower than interstriae, marked by circular and inconspicuous punctures on dorsal striae, well-defined in lateral striae; 
epipleura
and humeri glabrous.
